# Design tokens — additions to `src/app/globals.css`

The DS foundation requires a set of CSS custom properties under Tailwind's `@theme`
block. Merge the following into the existing `@theme` in `globals.css`.

If your project's `globals.css` doesn't yet have an `@theme` block, add one.

## What to add

```css
@import "tailwindcss";
@plugin "tailwindcss-animate";

@theme {
  /* -------------------------------------------------------------- */
  /* Brand colors — replace the hex values per project's brand.     */
  /* -------------------------------------------------------------- */
  --color-primary: #6e45ff;            /* primary actions, focus rings */
  --color-secondary: #ffc107;          /* secondary actions */
  --color-destructive: #dc2626;        /* errors, destructive actions */
  --color-muted: #f3f4f6;
  --color-muted-foreground: #6b7280;

  /* -------------------------------------------------------------- */
  /* DS palette — generate scales for the project's brand palette.  */
  /* These are the default Mrsanjob values; replace per project.    */
  /* -------------------------------------------------------------- */
  --color-ds-purple-50:  #f5f0ff;
  --color-ds-purple-100: #ebe0ff;
  --color-ds-purple-200: #d4c2ff;
  --color-ds-purple-300: #b09bff;
  --color-ds-purple-400: #8a72ff;
  --color-ds-purple-500: #6e45ff;
  --color-ds-purple-600: #5a36d6;
  --color-ds-purple-700: #4b2fad;

  --color-ds-yellow-200: #ffeeba;
  --color-ds-yellow-300: #ffe28a;
  --color-ds-yellow-400: #ffd35a;
  --color-ds-yellow-500: #ffc107;
  --color-ds-yellow-600: #f0b400;
  --color-ds-yellow-700: #ffae05;

  --color-ds-gray-200: #c8c8c8;
  --color-ds-gray-300: #a8a8a8;
  --color-ds-gray-400: #888888;
  --color-ds-gray-500: #666666;
  --color-ds-gray-600: #4c4c4c;
  --color-ds-gray-700: #3a3a3a;
  --color-ds-gray-800: #2c2c2c;

  /* -------------------------------------------------------------- */
  /* Input base tokens — used by _shared.ts variants.               */
  /* DO NOT REMOVE: the entire ds layer depends on these.           */
  /* -------------------------------------------------------------- */
  --base-width: 180px;
  --base-height: 48px;
  --base-radius: 8px;
  --base-opacity: 0.5;
  --base-border: rgba(93, 93, 93, 0.5);
  --base-text: #111111;
  --base-placeholder: rgba(93, 93, 93, 0.5);
}
```

## What this enables

After merging, the following Tailwind utility classes are available and used in
`_shared.ts`:

- `h-base-height` — 48px input height
- `min-w-base-width`, `w-base-width` — 180px min-width / fixed-width
- `rounded-base-radius` — 8px corner radius
- `opacity-base-opacity` — 0.5 for disabled states
- `border-base-border` — input border color
- `text-base-text`, `text-base-placeholder` — input text colors
- `bg-ds-purple-500`, `text-ds-yellow-700`, etc. — brand palette utilities

## Per-project customization

The locked **structure** is non-negotiable — every project has these tokens with
these names. The **values** are project-specific:

- Replace `--color-primary` and `--color-secondary` with the project's brand colors.
- Re-generate the `--color-ds-*` scales using your brand palette (50–700 for each
  brand color, plus a neutral gray scale).
- The `--base-*` tokens stay locked across projects. Inputs across all FE products
  share the same base size, radius, opacity, etc. — this is what makes the design
  system feel like a system.

If a project genuinely needs a different input height (e.g. a data-dense admin
panel), override at the variant level (custom `base` variant) — not by changing
`--base-height` globally. The token represents the project's primary input size.
